node.text: I remember exactly where I was when news of Whitney’s passing broke. I remember the immeasurable pain I felt and the shared loss it left on the world. Though I had never met my Whitney. Her music, beauty and talent had spoken to me throughout my childhood. The trauma of her past that lead to her drug abuse and eventual passing was something that resonated with me and I always felt a deep connection with her. I love Whitney Houston so so much and her legacy will always live on 🖤 #ripwhitneyhouston

node.text: This video of my niece being bullied has gone viral at her school this week. Promoting further bullying from the students there. Contrary to the stereotype we often see perpetuated of black women. My niece is a gentle, loving, kind and extremely smart young women. Her mother, who died earlier this year; Raised her to walk away from bullies, to not hit back, to ask for help from adults and to not engage. My darling niece I am so proud of you. You have been through so much trauma this year. Your family is so proud of you. Your mother would be so proud of you. To other young children out there getting bullied. ASK FOR HELP. DO NOT hit back. Karma will hit them back for you. That I promise. Your life will be full, you will get through this and you are not alone. To the bullies. I truly wish you love and happiness but SHAME ON YOU. To those filming, laughing, cheering. SHAME ON YOU. To the school, I want answers. @wematter

node.title: A video of my niece being bullied.

node.text:
I want to apologize on behalf of the media and the public for the decades long scrutiny and abuse you’ve had to endure. Zero compassion has ever been shown to a very young girl dealing with very public issues. Mental health is not for entertainment. This extremely unacceptable and inappropriate interview broke my heart. 

Framing Britney Spears has opened my eyes to the pain caused to these young women, the blatant misogyny in the media and the effects this may have on these young girls. I have seen first hand how this has impacted my friends; @lindsaylohan , @parishilton , @ritaora and I can’t begin to imagine what other celebrity women continue to endure today. 

We all need to start taking accountability for our words and our actions. Be Kind is not a trend 🖤 @iamenough

node.text: I feel so blessed that I get to walk through life with you. To have your love, joy and support is a honor that words could never describe. Thank you for continuing to inspire us all with your incredible work ethic, warm heart and your light that shines so brightly. The world sees a strong, funny, beautiful and successful superstar, all of which you are but it’s the vulnerable, sensitive and nurturing moments that has built our unbreakable bond. Have the most amazing day my bestie for life ❤️ I love you

node.text:
It’s vital to ‘Say it, Repeat It, Believe It, Share it’ @iamenough T shirt is OUT NOW (link in bio) and ALL PROCEEDS will be donated to the I AM ENOUGH FUND; providing FREE mental health resources to Black Communities.

Thank you @jodiesmith @ashleybanjogram @nathalieemmanuel @realevanross @_dilone @leighannepinnock @rickeythompson @rochellehumes @winnieharlow @alexandraburke @fleureast @leomieanderson and @sabrinaelba YOU ARE ENOUGH.

Today is National Suicide Prevention day. I urge you to check on your friends, even the “happy” ones. Reach out and let your friends know they are loved, they are valued and they are ENOUGH! If you’re going through a difficult time. Please know that you are NOT alone. We are with you. Reach out. We would rather hear about your struggles then your death. YOU ARE ENOUGH.

#NationalSuicidePreventionDay.

Video by @gerda_carina. Please visit iamenough.shop to support 🖤

node.title: PLEASE SHARE‼️ Mental Health Awareness Is Very Important

node.text: Thank you for giving my nephews and every young black boy and girl a superhero that looked just like them. Thank you for all that you contributed to Black Lives everywhere. Sending my thoughts, prayers and love to Chadwick’sfamily. Today we all lost our King 👑🖤🙏🏾 @iamenough
